  "prompt": "What are some unknown or underrated spots in Istanbul that one must visit?",
  "response": "Here are some less-known but fascinating spots in Istanbul:\n\n1. Hidden Gems\n- Balat neighborhood: Colorful historic streets with vintage houses\n- Kuzguncuk: Charming, peaceful neighborhood with historic wooden houses\n- Fener Greek Quarter: Historic area with beautiful architectural heritage\n\n2. Lesser-Known Historical Sites\n- Chora Church Museum (Kariye Museum): Byzantine-era church with stunning mosaics\n- S\u00fcleymaniye Hammam: Beautiful historic Turkish bath\n- B\u00fcy\u00fck Valide Han: Historic caravanserai with stunning rooftop views\n\n3. Unique Cultural Spots\n- SALT Galata: Contemporary art and research center\n- Istanbul Modern Art Museum\n- Pera Museum: Interesting exhibits and collections\n\n4. Off-Beaten Path Experiences\n- Princes' Islands: Tranquil car-free islands with historic mansions\n- Karak\u00f6y neighborhood: Hip area with street art and trendy cafes\n- Kad\u0131k\u00f6y market: Local, authentic market on the Asian side\n\n5. Natural Spots\n- Belgrad Forest: Large forest with hiking trails near the city\n- A\u011fva: Scenic coastal village north of Istanbul\n\nThese spots offer unique experiences beyond typical tourist attractions.",
